0,12,38,0.9); border:1px solid #313766;\">\n      <h3 style=\"font-size:1.02rem; margin-bottom:6px;\">Are online casinos legal for UK players in 2025?</h3>\n      <p><strong>Short answer:</strong> Yes \u2014 online casinos are legal in the UK when they are licensed and regulated by the UKGC.</p>\n      <p>\n        The UK has a long-established regulatory framework for online gambling overseen by the \n        <strong>UK Gambling Commission (UKGC)</strong>. Operators that hold a valid UKGC licence must follow strict rules \n        on player protection, safer gambling tools, advertising, KYC checks and withdrawal practices.  \n        Some British players also use offshore casinos, but these are not covered by the same level of UK oversight.\n      </p>\n      <p>\n        Player protection can vary widely between operators, so checking <strong>licensing status, payout \n        history and transparent terms</strong> matters far more than headline bonus size. For a broader overview of \n        regulation and safer gambling tools, see our\n        <a href=\"/responsible-gambling/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n          UK Safer Gambling &amp; Legal Guidance\n        </a>.\n      </p>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Q2 -->\n    <div class=\"tcs-faq-card\"\n         style=\"border-radius:16px; padding:18px 18px 20px; background:rgba(10,12,38,0.9); border:1px solid #313766;\">\n      <h3 style=\"font-size:1.02rem; margin-bottom:6px;\">What are the safest payment methods for UK players?</h3>\n      <p><strong>Short answer:</strong> Debit cards, e-wallets, bank transfer and, at some offshore casinos, crypto.</p>\n      <p>\n        UK-facing online casinos typically support <strong>Visa &amp; Mastercard debit cards</strong> (credit cards are not \n        allowed for gambling), <strong>PayPal, Skrill and Neteller</strong>, <strong>Revolut</strong>, <strong>Apple Pay</strong>, \n        standard <strong>bank transfers</strong> and, at some offshore brands, crypto options